{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "bricks", "icon": "VOP/bricks", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Bricks"], "extent": [63, 74]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Simulates an anti-aliased brick wall."], "extent": [74, 120]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator simulates an anti-aliased brick wall."], "extent": [120, 173]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Displacements are part of the features this operator offers, both in\nterms of groove depth (", {"type": "code", "text": ["gdepth"]}, ") and brick irregularity (", {"type": "code", "text": ["dscale"]}, "). To build\na separate displacement shader, use the Random Brick ID (id) and Groove\nAmount (", {"type": "code", "text": ["amount"]}, ") outputs."], "extent": [173, 419]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["To add randomness to the shape of each brick, create a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvnoise", "type": "link", "text": ["UV Noise"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvnoise"}, "\noperator, lower its frequency parameter and connect its ", {"type": "q", "text": ["news"]}, " and newt\"\noutputs into the S and T (s t) Coordinate inputs."], "extent": [419, 626]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the Position (", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, "), Normal (", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, ") and texture coordinate (s t) inputs are\nnot connected, the global variables by the same names will be used\ninstead. Typically, you will use ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "type": "link", "text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "type": "link", "text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, " as\ninputs for ", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, ", and Shading Layer Parameter as the input for ", {"type": "code", "text": ["s"]}, " and\n", {"type": "code", "text": ["t"]}, ". You will not touch ", {"type": "code", "text": ["N"]}, " unless you want to apply additional\ndisplacement to the brick surface using an operator such as ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise", "type": "link", "text": ["Bump Noise"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise"}, "\nor ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/cavities", "type": "link", "text": ["Cavities"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/cavities"}, ". If you need to access the global variables directly, they\nare available from the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global"}, " operator."], "extent": [626, 1264]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Other materials that can be simulated with this operator include asphalt\nshingles and cinder blocks. Here is a list of suggested values several\nsuch materials:"], "extent": [1264, 1425]}, {"lang": null, "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nMaterial            bcolor1       bcolor2          gcolor  gwidth \ngdepth dfreq  damp dchip dscale\n---------------+---------------+----------------+---------+-------+------+-----+-----+-----+------\n        Red Brick       .883 .239 .147   .667 .269 .111  .3 .3 .3   .05\n    .03    2.6   1.5   .3    .5\n        Beige Brick     .619 .566 .540   .700 .600 .500  .4 .3 .3   .05\n    .03    2.6   1.5   .3    .5\n        Brown Brick     .545 .352    0   .387 .251    0  .3 .2 .1   .05\n    .03    2.6   1.5   .3    .5\n        Asphalt Shingle .335 .335 .335   .423 .423 .440  .3 .3 .3   .01\n    .01    3.2   1.7   .1   -.1\n        Cinder Block    .582 .582 .582   .423 .423 .440  .5 .5 .5   .05\n    .03    2.6   1.5   .3    .5\n        \n"], "extent": [1425, 2160]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2160, 2171], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/bricker", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bricker"}], "extent": [2171, 2193]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/bumpnoise"}], "extent": [2193, 2216]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/concrete", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/concrete"}], "extent": [2216, 2238]}, {"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}], "extent": [2238, 2260]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Bricks"], "summary": ["Simulates an anti-aliased brick wall."]}